: 6115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.366247096901434e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6023}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 6024, \"to\": 6052}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium setting\", \"from\": 6074, \"to\": 6091}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 6096, \"to\": 6100}, {\"ngram\": \"Games Wide Open\", \"from\": 6136, \"to\": 6151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 10,500 athletes will parade through the heart of the French capital onboats on the Seinealong a 6-kilometer (3.7-mile) route.\", \"from\": 6154, \"to\": 6285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6213, \"end\": 6219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9683811175729827, \"rank\": 0.028892181211461636, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"About 10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 6154, \"to\": 6175}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 6196, \"to\": 6205}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seinealong\", \"from\": 6239, \"to\": 6253}, {\"ngram\": \"a 6-kilometer (3.7-mile) route\", \"from\": 6254, \"to\": 6284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 160 heads of state are expected to attend, and the government will close all airports and airspace within a 150-kilometer (90-mile) radius around Paris before, during and after the 3\\u00bd-hour ceremony.\", \"from\": 6287, \"to\": 6491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6439, \"end\": 6444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.366247096901434e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"About 160 heads\", \"from\": 6287, \"to\": 6302}, {\"ngram\": \"state\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6311}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 6340, \"to\": 6354}, {\"ngram\": \"all airports\", \"from\": 6366, \"to\": 6378}, {\"ngram\": \"airspace\", \"from\": 6383, \"to\": 6391}, {\"ngram\": \"a 150-kilometer (90-mile) radius\", \"from\": 6399, \"to\": 6431}, {\"ngram\": \"the 3\\u00bd-hour ceremony\", \"from\": 6470, \"to\": 6490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 2,500 foreign police will be among the 45,000 security force members deployed around Paris for the event, Darmanin said.\", \"from\": 6493, \"to\": 6620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6585, \"end\": 6590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.366247096901434e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Around 2,500 foreign police\", \"from\": 6493, \"to\": 6520}, {\"ngram\": \"the 45,000 security force members\", \"from\": 6535, \"to\": 6568}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 6595, \"to\": 6604}, {\"ngram\": \"Darmanin\", \"from\": 6606, \"to\": 6614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discussion is underway on whether the foreign forces can board the boats with their countries' athletes, and what arms they can carry.\", \"from\": 6621, \"to\": 6755, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Discussion\", \"from\": 6621, \"to\": 6631}, {\"ngram\": \"the foreign forces\", \"from\": 6655, \"to\": 6673}, {\"ngram\": \"the boats\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6693}, {\"ngram\": \"their countries' athletes\", \"from\": 6699, \"to\": 6724}, {\"ngram\": \"what arms\", \"from\": 6730, \"to\": 6739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hiring and training enough security personnel for the Olympics, held from July 26-Aug. 11 and the subsequent Paralympics has proved challenging.\", \"from\": 6757, \"to\": 6901, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram